      <hedline>
        <hl1>Respect for Serbs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard Sexton letter disputes October 16 Op-Ed article by Sens Mitch McConnell and Pat Leahy demanding that Serbia hand over Slobodan Milosevic and other suspected war criminals to International War Crimes Tribunal as condition for receiving economic aid</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I take issue with the statement by Senators Mitch McConnell and Patrick Leahy (Op-Ed, Oct. 16) that Yugoslavia must ''hand over'' Slobodan Milosevic and other suspected war criminals to the International War Crimes Tribunal at The Hague in order to earn the economic ''rewards'' that, admittedly, the Yugoslavs deserve.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I take issue with the statement by Senators Mitch McConnell and Patrick Leahy (Op-Ed, Oct. 16) that Yugoslavia must ''hand over'' Slobodan Milosevic and other suspected war criminals to the International War Crimes Tribunal at The Hague in order to earn the economic ''rewards'' that, admittedly, the Yugoslavs deserve.</p>
        <p>We are a better nation than that. We made war on these people, and we should be magnanimous victors, not bullies rubbing their noses in the dirt. Why not give the new democratically elected government some slack and some respect?</p>
        <p>Any trial of Mr. Milosevic should be conducted in Yugoslavia before Serbian judges. Instead of having foreigners enforce their judgment on a demonized enemy, let Serbs deal with the problem in full perspective -- so Serbs can come to terms with the horrors that Mr. Milosevic provoked and allowed in their name.</p>
        <p>RICHARD SEXTON  Brooklyn, Oct. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
